race.comment: TONKIN (9) Victorian-trained mare who resumes with excellent sprint figures. Went quickly through the grades last prep, including an unlucky second to Persian Spirit from an outside draw at Flemington. Recent trial win over 900m at Rosehill had merit and will prove hard to catch. HAWKER HALL (7) kept fresh for this after surging to the front from the sticky gate with a decisive win in fast time over 1200m at the Gold Coast MM Carnival. Well placed at this trip and kept up to the mark with an 850m trial win. Go close. WONDEREACH (10) had excuses when he lost the near fore plate in the run with a fading ninth at Eagle Farm. One for the exotics. KERGUELEN (2) boasts a strong first-up record and he's not to be discounted.
